  "blogs": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "slug": "art-of-modern-tailoring",
      "author": "Marcus Sterling",
      "authorImage": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1472099645785-5658abf4ff4e?w=100&h=100&fit=crop",
      "date": "April 05, 2026",
      "category": "Design",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594938298603-c8148c4dae35?w=1200&auto=format&fit=crop",
      "readingTime": "6 min read",
      "relatedProductIds": [101, 103, 110],
      "en": {
        "title": "The Art of Modern Tailoring",
        "excerpt": "Crafting the perfect silhouette through Japanese precision and Italian heritage.",
        "content": "<p class='lead'>Tailoring is more than just construction; it is an architectural dialogue between the body and the fabric. In this editorial, we explore the meticulous process behind our seasonal outerwear collection.</p><h3>The Material Source</h3><p>Our journey begins in the historic mills of Biella, Italy, where the world's finest virgin wool is woven. We select weights that offer structure without rigidity, allowing the garment to move with the wearer.</p><h3>Japanese Precision</h3><p>While our fabrics are Italian, our construction methodology is deeply rooted in Japanese minimalism. Every shoulder seam, every internal canvas, and every hand-finished buttonhole is considered.</p><ul><li>Double-faced wool construction for seamless warmth</li><li>Floating canvas for natural drape over time</li><li>Sustainable horn buttons sourced from ethical producers</li></ul>"
      },
      "ar": {
        "title": "فن التفصيل الحديث",
        "excerpt": "صياغة المظهر المثالي من خلال الدقة اليابانية والتراث الإيطالي.",
        "content": "<p class='lead'>التفصيل هو أكثر من مجرد بناء؛ إنه حوار معماري بين الجسد والقماش. في هذه الافتتاحية، نستكشف العملية الدقيقة وراء مجموعة الملابس الخارجية الموسمية لدينا.</p><h3>مصدر المادة</h3><p>تبدأ رحلتنا في المصانع التاريخية في بييلا، إيطاليا، حيث يتم نسج أفضل صوف بكر في العالم. نختار الأوزان التي توفر الهيكل دون صلابة.</p><h3>الدقة اليابانية</h3><p>بينما أقمشتنا إيطالية، فإن منهجية البناء لدينا متجذرة بعمق في البساطة اليابانية. يتم النظر في كل خط كتف، وكل قطعة داخلية، وكل عروة زر مشطبة يدوياً.</p>"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "slug": "minimalist-capsule-wardrobe",
      "author": "Elena Rossi",
      "authorImage": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1438761681033-6461ffad8d80?w=100&h=100&fit=crop",
      "date": "April 02, 2026",
      "category": "Lifestyle",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1596755094514-f87e34085b2c?w=1200&auto=format&fit=crop",
      "readingTime": "4 min read",
      "relatedProductIds": [102, 106, 112],
      "en": {
        "title": "Building a Minimalist Capsule Wardrobe",
        "excerpt": "Simplify your morning routine with intentionally selected essentials.",
        "content": "<p>The concept of a capsule wardrobe is not about restriction—it's about freedom. By choosing fewer, better pieces, you create a modular system where everything works together.</p><h3>The Foundation</h3><p>Start with the pieces that touch your skin. Our Supima cotton basics and raw selvedge denim form the core of any functional wardrobe. These are the workhorses that age beautifully and never go out of style.</p><h3>Interchangeability</h3><p>A true capsule relies on a consistent color palette. We focus on earthy neutrals, deep indigos, and crisp whites to ensure that regardless of what you pull from the rack, the combination is intentional.</p>"
      },
      "ar": {
        "title": "بناء خزانة ملابس بسيطة",
        "excerpt": "بسط روتينك الصباحي مع أساسيات مختارة بعناية.",
        "content": "<p>مفهوم خزانة الملابس المصغرة لا يتعلق بالتقييد بل بالحرية. من خلال اختيار قطع أقل وأفضل، فإنك تخلق نظاماً معيارياً حيث يعمل كل شيء معاً.</p>"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "slug": "sustainable-luxury",
      "author": "Julian Vane",
      "authorImage": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500648767791-00dcc994a43e?w=100&h=100&fit=crop",
      "date": "March 28, 2026",
      "category": "Philosophy",
      "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1523381210434-271e8be1f52b?w=1200&auto=format&fit=crop",
      "readingTime": "8 min read",
      "relatedProductIds": [104, 107, 109, 105],
      "en": {
        "title": "Sustainable Luxury: The New Paradigm",
        "excerpt": "Why ethical craftsmanship is the ultimate expression of refinement.",
        "content": "<p>Luxury in the 21st century is defined by transparency. Knowing who made your clothes and the environmental impact of the fibers is as essential as the design itself.</p><h3>Mulberry Silk & Mongolian Cashmere</h3><p>We work directly with cooperatives to source our natural fibers. This direct-to-mill approach ensures fair wages for artisans and the preservation of traditional pastoral methods.</p><h3>Beyond the Garment</h3><p>Sustainability extends to our packaging and longevity. Our wool trousers and silk blouses are designed to be repaired, not replaced, fostering a circular approach to fashion.</p>"
      },
      "ar": {
        "title": "الفخامة المستدامة: النموذج الجديد",
        "excerpt": "لماذا تعتبر الحرفية الأخلاقية التعبير النهائي عن الرقي.",
        "content": "<p>يتم تعريف الفخامة في القرن الحادي والعشرين من خلال الشفافية. معرفة من صنع ملابسك والأثر البيئي للألياف أمر ضروري تماماً مثل التصميم نفسه.</p>"
      }
    }
  ],

